==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cenozoic
<hw>Ce`no*zo"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ recent +
<?/ life.]</ety> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>Belonging to the most recent
division of geological time, including the tertiary, or Age of mammals,
and the Quaternary, or Age of man. <altsp>[Written also
<asp>c⟦ae⟧nozoic</asp>, <asp>cainozoic</asp>,
<asp>kainozoic</asp>.]</altsp> See <er>Geology</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ This word is used by many authors as synonymous with
<xex>Tertiary</xex>, the Quaternary Age not being included.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cense</ent>⟦br⟧
